claim.claim-text:
1. A portable hoist assembly comprising: 
a. a base member capable of being coupled with a receiving member; 
b. a support member coupled to said base member; 
c. a boom coupled to said support member, and said boom and base member are pivotal with respect to said support member, for collapsing the hoist assembly to a storage position; 
d. a winch assembly, having a line thereon, connected to the support member and the boom; 
e. an engagement member connected to the line, and said engagement member capable of fitting within one of said base member, support member or boom for storage thereof.

10. A portable hoist assembly comprising: 
a. a base member capable of being supported in a receiving member; 
b. a support member coupled to said base member and said base member is pivotal with respect to said support member; 
c. a boom coupled to said support member, distal to the base member, and said boom is pivotal respect to the support member; 
d. a winch assembly, having line thereon, connected to the support member and the boom; 
e. an engagement member connected to said line and said engagement member is capable of being inserted into said base member for storage; and, 
g. a storage position for the hoist assembly wherein said base member, support member and boom are collapsed in said storage position and said boom having an end inserted into said base member, and said boom and base member extend substantially parallel to the support member.

17. A portable hoist assembly mountable on a vehicle, comprising: 
a. a receiving member mounted on a vehicle; 
b. a base member coupled with said receiving member; 
c. a support member coupled to the base member in a substantially vertical position, and pivotal with respect to the base member to collapse the hoist assembly to a storage position; 
d. a winch assembly, having a line thereon, connected to the support member; and, 
e. an engagement member connected to the line and winch assembly and said engagement member capable of fitting within said base member, boom or support member when hoist assembly is in a storage position.

20. A method of storing a portable hoist assembly, said portable hoist having a base member pivotally mounted to an upright support member, and said support member includes a first support member attached to the base member and a second support member in sliding engagement with the first support member, and a boom member pivotally mounted to the second support member, comprising the steps of: 
a. pivoting a base member to a position substantially parallel to the support member; 
b. pivoting the boom to a position substantially parallel to the support member; 
c. sliding the second support member toward said base member; 
d. connecting an end of the boom member with the base member; and 
e. locking the second support member to the first support member.
